name: central cityapartement- wifi- nice neighbourhood
description: 39m² apartment with beautiful courtyard of the house. quiet and safe upcoming neighborhood-located in old jewish quater and popular area of Vienna. Surrounded by nice bars and restaurants, 15 min walkingdistance to the middle of citycenter, close to many sights . 300m  to subway U2 Taborstraße. Next to the karmelitermarket (with delicious places to eat) and the Augarten. free wifi. touristtax of 3,2% is included in the price.
neighborhood_overview: the Karmeliterviertel became very popular in the last years. It offers many new pubs and restaurants and is located next to Augarten (huge garden good for jogging), to the concert hall of Wiener Sängerknaben (muth), and has the Karmelitermarket, which is best to visit on Saturday morning to get biological products. In summer the best nightbars are at the donaukanal, which is 5 minutes away.
host_about:
I am open minded and like travelling myself. I have spent many months in Latinamerica and Asia, where I got  in touch with Indian philosophie and meditation...
Now I mostly work in the field of contemporary art and I do my best to offer you a nice apartment next to the citycenter...!

name: The WHITE Apartment | Prater Ferris Wheel
description:
Bright spacious 2-room apartment.
With only 1 min walk to 2 different metros; ride only 1 station to the city center.

Prater Ferris Wheel, Wien Messe convention center, Vienna International Center, and Saint Stephen's Cathedral are easily accessible!

FYI: They are making wider bicycle lanes and planting more trees just outside our building. We cannot control which side of the street it happens and when. Its not suitable for daytime sleepers or guests who need to study/work during their stay!
neighborhood_overview:
Supermarkets, bars and eateries are very closeby.

3 mins walk away you have the Prater which is the biggest park in Vienna - Walking, jogging, cycling, soccer, frisbee, horse riding - Whatever lights your inner fire ;)

Very close is the first district as well as the United Nations building and Vienna International Center and Messe Wien where lots of conferences are held.
host_about:
Welcome to Zen Apartments!

We strive to enable comfortable and enjoyable stay away from your home.

name: Premium Apartment At The Belvedere – 60m²
description: Immerse yourself in the vibrant energy of Vienna and escape from the hustle and bustle of daily life with a truly luxurious stay in our premium apartment. Boasting a spacious living and dining room complete with a fully-equipped kitchenette, a cozy sleeping area and a beautifully presented bathroom with a walk-in shower, this charming holiday retreat effortlessly blends modern residential amenities with the innate allure of the city.
neighborhood_overview:
Venture into the Fasanviertel neighborhood, where the grandeur of the Belvedere palaces and the tranquility of Vienna's botanical gardens await. In this historic residential district, you'll find an array of grocery stores, drugstores, pharmacy, eateries, and cafés and much more. You're also very close to the Botschaftsviertel (Embassy district) where countries sit – in beautiful buildings – peacefully, it seems, next to each other. The Arsenal on the other end is not only a nice part but home an historic museum.
Also, mind you are in walking distance (10 mins) to the very heart of Vienna
host_about: Ich mag Reisen, Lesen und  Filme. Und ich bin neugierig auf neue Länder und interessante Menschen.

name: IVORY TOWER - sunny, cosy, spacious
description:
A beautiful 100 sqm 19th-century building with high rooms and wooden floors can become your new home in Vienna!
Bright, spacious apartment, totally central, Ferris wheel just around the corner: Your perfect feel-good home base!
This listing is an insider tip because it's not an anonymous Ikea rental apartment but rather the real center of our lives when we're not abroad.
Booking duration at least 3 weeks.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located in the middle of the second district, the trendy district of the city:
- In just a few minutes' walk you are in the inner old town and at St. Stephen's Cathedral, organic farmers' market and many shopping opportunities everywhere
- The incredibly beautiful Prater recreation area right on your doorstep! Jogging, roller skating, swimming, hiking, etc. - everything is possible!

name: Cozy Studio in the City Centre
description:
Fully equipped, newly renovated and charming apartment in the trendy, central Jewish Quarter. Cafes, good restaurants, public transport (SUBWAY LINE U1 is just down the street) and most of Vienna's top attractions are within easy walking distance.

This is a cozy shelter for travelers who want to be in the middle of the city, yet have a quiet space to relax. It has a private entrance, a newly renovated kitchen and all the amenities needed for a city getaway.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is in a lovely part of Vienna in the Jewish Quarter of the city. It has a pleasant combination of a traditional feel (with old shops, synagogues, and old traditional houses) with the up-and-coming vibe of a trendy neighborhood filled with picturesque cafes and chic restaurants of all kinds.

The location is perfect to explore Vienna. It is within walking distance to the main tourist sites like Stephansplatz, the Giant Ferris Wheel in Praterstern, the beautiful Augarten Park and the many museums and sites in the city center. Just stroll across the famous "Donaukanal – Danube canal" with its beautiful parklike surrounding and its lively atmosphere, and, for a once-in-a-lifetime splurge, the apartment is 4 minutes away from the luxurious Sofitel roof-top restaurant where you can enjoy gourmet food while watching the whole city from above (you can also just go for a drink).
host_about:
I am originally from Latin America, but have lived in Vienna since 2010. I love traveling, especially in India and Myanmar, where I fell in love with yoga and meditation practices. 

I studied Literature and love poetry, fiction and song lyrics from different cultures and epochs. I have a job at the United Nations in Vienna and during my free time, I try to explore beautiful cities and countrysides, spend time with my daughter and, as of lately, host Airbnb travelers.

neighborhood_overview:
Neubau ( District 7) akin to some of the more vibrant neighborhoods you might find around London’s South East or Berlin, with throngs of independent shops, galleries, and cafes frequented by well-clad youths. The seventh district, like any gentrified area, hasn’t always been this way.

Art:
-Vienna’s art scene has always been fruitful, boasting a long reigning reputation for producing and showcasing talent. Tearing tourists away from the seventh’s Museumsquartier is no easy feat—however, just around the corner in the backstreets, lives a melting pot of aesthetic goodness for those with a creative temperament; a torrent of smaller galleries and street art.

Food and Drink:
-Along the main strips of Neubaugasse, new restaurants and cafes are constantly popping up, pushing the area into being one of the most desirable in Vienna’s culinary scene. Cafe Espresso, on Burggasse, has the feeling of being a typical Viennese coffee house with a touch of insomnia. Pos
